===Trivia===
{{lang|ja|死ぬ}} is the only modern Japanese verb which ends in {{m|ja|ぬ}} (an older example is {{m|ja|去ぬ||to go, to leave|tr=inu}}, which is now archaic). Accordingly, it is often used in textbooks to illustrate the conjugation pattern for {{lang|ja|〜ぬ}} verbs.

